dy of motorcycle taxi drivers in Bangkok. Claudio Sopranzetti advances an analysis of power that focuses not on the sturdiness of hegemony or the ubiquity of everyday resistance but on its potential fragility and the work needed for its maintenance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aDemonstrationszThailandxHistoryy21st century. 0aMotorcyclistszThailandzBangkok. 0aPolitical violencezThailandzBangkok. 0aTaxicab driverszThailandzBangkok. 70(DE-601)1041522060(DE-588)4046514-7aPolitik2gnd 70(DE-601)1041807220(DE-588)4123438-8aInteressenkonflikt2gnd 70(DE-601)10432967X0(DE-588)4277493-7aPolitische Mobilisierung2gnd 70(DE-601)1060797270(DE-588)4077574-4aSoziale Schichtung2gnd 70(DE-601)1061006610(DE-588)4070285-6aDemonstration2gnd 70(DE-601)1061442780(DE-588)4059186-4aTaxifahrer2gnd 70(DE-601)10631663X0(DE-588)4020832-1aGewalt2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520963399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780520963399.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles